This paper deals with pedestrian detection and person recognition using convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as discriminatively trained ID-discriminative Embedding (IDE) and Confidence Weighted Similarity (CWS) metric, which are relevant to the machine learning (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the evaluation of detector performance, which is relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the issue of assessing the effectiveness of different detectors, which is relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
